question.text: Identify the option with correct labelings A-F from the given diagram of castor seed.

options.text: A-Testa, B-Endosperm, C-Cotyledon, D-Tegmen, E-Radicle, F-Caruncle.
A-Tegmen, B-Endosperm, C-Cotyledon, D-Testa, E-Radicle, F-Caruncle.
A-Tegmen, B-Endosperm, C-Cotyledon, D-Testa, E-Plumule, F-Caruncle.
A-Testa, B-Endosperm, C-Cotyledon, D-Tegmen, E-Plumule, F-Caruncle.

solution.text: Castor (Ricinus communis) is an example of a dicot plant in which endosperm is persistent in the seed. Thus, it is a type of endospermic or albuminous seed. There are two cotyledons in the seed and endosperm is not used up completely by the developing embryo.
